config.prompt:
Generate the docs file for the component '{{ component.id }}' based on the refined spec and provided diagrams.
Where appropriate, include any of the diagrams that would be important for consumers/users of this component, but not the ones only needed by implementers of the component.
<REFINED_SPEC>
{{ refined_spec }}
</REFINED_SPEC>
<COMPONENT>
{{ component }}
</COMPONENT>
<DIAGRAMS>
{{ diagrams }}
</DIAGRAMS>
<PHILOSOPHY_GUIDES>
[IMPLEMENTATION] {{ implementation_philosophy }}
[MODULAR] {{ modular_design_philosophy }}
[DOCS_GUIDE] {{ component_docs_spec_guide }}
</PHILOSOPHY_GUIDES>
Save as '{{ component.id }}_docs.md'.

Generate the spec file for the component '{{ component.id }}' based on the refined spec, component docs, and provided diagrams.
Include any of the diagrams that were not used by the docs file for this component, so that they are available to the implementer who will get both the docs and spec file for their context.
<REFINED_SPEC>
{{ refined_spec }}
</REFINED_SPEC>
<COMPONENT>
{{ component }}
</COMPONENT>
<DIAGRAMS>
{{ diagrams }}
</DIAGRAMS>
<COMPONENT_DOCS>
{{ docs_file[0].content }}
</COMPONENT_DOCS>
<PHILOSOPHY_GUIDES>
[IMPLEMENTATION] {{ implementation_philosophy }}
[MODULAR] {{ modular_design_philosophy }}
[DOCS_GUIDE] {{ component_docs_spec_guide }}
</PHILOSOPHY_GUIDES>
Empty arrays should be rendered as the string **None** under their respective sections. Save as '{{ component.id }}_spec.md'.
